# MVP Spec ‚Äî Personalized Plan + Today‚Äôs Session (Gym-style Web Prototype)

Owner: You  
Implementers: Claude + Codex  
Platform: Web (mobile-first), runs locally, **no database** (state in `localStorage`)  
Goal: Demonstrate **core logic + UX** of a ‚Äúpersonalized program‚Äù funnel: value preview ‚Üí email save ‚Üí locked plan ‚Üí paywall imitation ‚Üí full unlocked plan.

---

## 1) What we are building

A mobile-first web app that:
1) Accepts Gym-funnel answers (as JSON) via a dev harness form.
2) Calls a Large Language Model (LLM) to generate a structured **7-day plan**.
3) Shows **Day 1** immediately (value first).
4) Optionally asks email to ‚Äúsave your plan‚Äù.
5) Shows Days 2‚Äì7 locked; tapping locked days opens a paywall imitation.
6) After ‚ÄúContinue‚Äù on paywall (no real payment), unlocks full plan and enables ‚Äúsession player‚Äù + completion + check-in, stored locally.

This aligns with the key funnel insight: users convert better when the paid offer is **concrete** (‚Äúyour program is ready‚Äù) and when they can see value before committing.

